  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, you mentioned an API issue — how's the wait going? I enjoy solving tech hiccups with a hot cup of tea. What's your go-to drink?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Tea, obviously! No work for me without it. Sometimes add a dash of milk — *chai* is life. How about you? Any specific tea you like during tech troubles?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds perfect — tea and code go well together, I think. I love the first Sui Dhaaga movie, how it tells simple stories with real feelings. What's your take on it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, I haven't watched Sui Dhaaga myself, but I know many people liked it for its soft and gentle story. I usually prefer action or comedy, like some Bollywood ones. Maybe something like *Dilwale* or *PK* for a laugh. Do you watch a lot of Bollywood?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said \"I haven't watched Sui Dhaaga myself\" — and that's clear. Action and comedy are fun choices. I get that — sometimes you just want a good laugh. What's your favourite Bollywood comedy?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "*Dilwale* is a solid pick, but I'd say *Lagaan* has some iconic comedy moments too — especially the village elders acting all serious. Also, *Chennai Express* with Salman Khan is a crowd-pleaser. But maybe I should try more dramas like Sui Dhaaga sometime. What made you like it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Lagaan’s village elders are a classic — hilarious! I get why you like it. Sui Dhaaga moved me with its small-town warmth. It felt real, not too flashy. What draws you to action or comedy over dramas?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Action and comedy give me that instant escape, you know? Maybe I'm just not a heavy drama person. I like my stories to have some zing — whether it's a fast-paced cricket match or a funny scene. But I can see how dramas like Sui Dhaaga bring a different kind of joy. Maybe I'll give it a try sometime!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that — instant escape is great after a tough day. Cricket matches and zingy scenes are perfect for a quick boost. Give Sui Dhaaga a try sometime — you might find a new corner of joy. What movie are you watching next?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I was thinking of watching *Brahmāstra* again — it's a fantasy action film with some good comedy bits too. Maybe not as gentle as Sui Dhaaga, but it's fun. Have you seen it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Brahmāstra sounds like a fun pick — fantasy with some laughs is a good mix. I haven’t seen it, but I’m all for a good entertaining watch. What part of the movie do you enjoy most — action, comedy, or the story?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The action scenes are the highlight for me — all the big visuals and stunts are a treat to watch. Salman Khan and Amitabh Bachchan’s chemistry adds a nice touch too. Maybe one day I’ll try a more gentle movie like you said. Thanks for the suggestion!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said \"the action scenes are the highlight\" — and that's clear. Salman and Amitabh’s team-up is always fun to watch. Maybe next time, a gentle story with some laughs? What’s on your list for the weekend?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Weekend plans? Probably some cricket on TV and maybe a movie marathon — though I might stick to action-comedy for now! But I'll keep Sui Dhaaga in mind. Thanks again!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Cricket and movie marathons sound like a perfect weekend. I get that — comfort picks are the best. Let me know how the cricket action is. Watching Sui Dhaaga anytime soon?"
